  "version": 14,
  "html": "<article class=\"max-w-4xl mx-auto\">\n\n  \n  <section class=\"gradient-flame-sunglow text-white p-5 md:p-10 rounded-2xl mb-8\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold mb-4 text-white\">Look, the Grid Isn't Getting Better Anytime Soon</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed opacity-95\">\n      If you've spent any time on the phone with family in Cuba lately, you already know. Eight-hour blackouts aren't the exception anymore—they're Tuesday. And Wednesday. And probably Thursday too. Solar panels went from \"nice to have\" to \"how is abuela keeping her insulin cold\" real fast. The good news? The tech has gotten dramatically better and more affordable. The tricky part is figuring out what actually makes sense to ship—because not every panel that works great in Arizona is going to survive Cuban humidity, customs scrutiny, or the reality of installation without a professional electrician nearby.\n    </p>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none mb-10\">\n    <p>\n      Here's what nobody tells you about solar panels for Cuba: wattage isn't everything. A 400W panel sounds impressive until you realize it weighs 50 pounds and your shipping costs just doubled. Or worse—it's rigid glass that'll crack if the package gets tossed around in customs (and it will get tossed around in customs). The sweet spot for most families is somewhere between portability and power output, with serious attention paid to durability.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      The other thing worth knowing: Cuba runs on 110V and 220V depending on the neighborhood and the mood of the infrastructure gods that day. Most modern solar setups handle this fine, but you'll want a charge controller that can manage the chaos. And if your family doesn't have someone handy with electrical work, foldable plug-and-play systems are worth their weight in gold—literally easier to set up than assembling IKEA furniture.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      I've gone through the current options and sorted them by what actually matters: <strong>shipping practicality</strong>, <strong>durability in tropical conditions</strong>, <strong>ease of setup</strong>, and <strong>bang for your watt</strong>. Let's get into it.\n    </p>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"bg-sunglow/10 border-2 border-sunglow p-5 md:p-8 rounded-xl mb-10\">\n    <h3 class=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-raisin dark:text-white mb-3\">The Short Version</h3>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 text-base md:text-lg mb-4\">\n      For most families, the <strong>Renogy 400W Portable Solar Panel Blanket</strong> hits the sweet spot—25% efficiency, folds down to nothing for shipping, and sets up without tools. If budget matters more than portability, the <strong>ECO-WORTHY 400W Kit</strong> gives you more watts per dollar but requires actual installation.\n    </p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0F4JR1PFM?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-block px-6 py-3 rounded-full bg-flame text-white font-semibold no-underline hover:bg-flame/90 transition-colors\">\n      See the Top Pick on Amazon\n    </a>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"mb-12\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-raisin dark:text-white mb-6\">The One to Beat</h2>\n    \n    <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-xl ring-2 ring-lime ring-offset-2 ring-offset-white dark:ring-offset-slate-900\">\n      <span class=\"bg-lime text-raisin px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase mb-4 inline-block\">Editor's Pick</span>\n      <div class=\"flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6\">\n        <div class=\"w-full md:w-64 shrink-0\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71JVhqo2kjL._AC_SR160,134_CB1169409_QL70_.jpg\" alt=\"Renogy 400W Portable Solar Panel Blanket - Best solar panel for Cuba\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-xl w-full h-64 object-contain bg-slate-50\" />\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n          <h3 class=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-raisin dark:text-white mb-2\" data-asin=\"B0F4JR1PFM\">Renogy 400W Portable Solar Panel Blanket</h3>\n          <div class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 mb-4\">\n            <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold\">4.6★</span>\n            <span class=\"text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">$$$$$ tier</span>\n            <span class=\"bg-royal/10 text-royal px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-medium\">N-Type • 25% Efficiency</span>\n          </div>\n          <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4\">\n            This thing folds 16 times. Sixteen. It goes from a 400-watt powerhouse to something you can actually fit in a suitcase or ship without paying freight costs. The N-Type cells are the latest tech—better performance in partial shade (which matters when you're positioning panels on a Cuban rooftop with random trees and water tanks in the way). IP65 waterproof rating means it'll handle the summer storms.\n          </p>\n          <p class=\"font-bold text-flame mb-4\">\n            VERDICT: The shipping-friendly champion. Maximum power, minimum headache.\n          </p>\n          <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0F4JR1PFM?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-block px-6 py-3 rounded-full bg-flame text-white font-semibold no-underline hover:bg-flame/90 transition-colors\">\n            Check Price on Amazon\n          </a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <blockquote class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl italic text-flame border-l-4 border-flame pl-6 my-10\">\n    \"Eight-hour blackouts aren't the exception anymore—they're the schedule.\"\n  </blockquote>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"mb-12\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-raisin dark:text-white mb-6\">Best Value: More Watts, Less Cash</h2>\n    \n    <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-xl ring-2 ring-sunglow ring-offset-2 ring-offset-white dark:ring-offset-slate-900 mb-6\">\n      <span class=\"bg-sunglow text-raisin px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase mb-4 inline-block\">Best Value</span>\n      <div class=\"flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6\">\n        <div class=\"w-full md:w-64 shrink-0\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71Y2w0CVuKL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"ECO-WORTHY 400W Solar Panels Kit - Best value for Cuba\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-xl w-full h-64 object-contain bg-slate-50\" />\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n          <h3 class=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-raisin dark:text-white mb-2\" data-asin=\"B0CYH13JJK\">ECO-WORTHY 400W Solar Panels (4x 100W)</h3>\n          <div class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 mb-4\">\n            <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold\">4.5★</span>\n            <span class=\"text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">$$$$$ tier • 455 reviews</span>\n          </div>\n          <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4\">\n            Four separate 100W panels means flexibility—you can install them in different spots, replace one if it gets damaged, or ship them in separate packages to stay under weight limits. The monocrystalline cells are proven tech, nothing fancy but reliable. The catch? These are rigid panels. Someone's going to need to mount them properly.\n          </p>\n          <p class=\"font-bold text-flame mb-4\">\n            VERDICT: The practical choice when you've got someone handy on the other end.\n          </p>\n          <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CYH13JJK?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-block px-6 py-3 rounded-full bg-flame text-white font-semibold no-underline hover:bg-flame/90 transition-colors\">\n            Check Price on Amazon\n          </a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"my-10\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-raisin dark:text-white mb-4\">How Much Solar Does Your Family Actually Need?</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-6\">Plug in the typical blackout hours and see what setup makes sense:</p>\n    <solar-sizing>\n  </solar-sizing></section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"mb-12\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-raisin dark:text-white mb-6\">The Portable Panel Showdown</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-6\">If shipping weight and ease of setup are your priorities, these three go head-to-head:</p>\n    \n    <div class=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6\">\n      \n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71ywtVtTIaL._AC_SR160,134_CB1169409_QL70_.jpg\" alt=\"Renogy 200W Portable Solar Panel\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-48 object-contain bg-slate-50 mb-4\" />\n        <h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-raisin dark:text-white mb-2\" data-asin=\"B0CNPHD4VY\">Renogy 200W Portable</h3>\n        <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold\">4.5★</span>\n        <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 text-sm mt-3 mb-4\">\n          The starter option. IP65 waterproof, foldable, works with most power stations. Good for keeping phones charged and running a fan—not enough for a fridge.\n        </p>\n        <p class=\"text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 mb-3\">Best for: Small apartments, backup power</p>\n        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CNPHD4VY?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"text-flame font-semibold text-sm hover:underline\">View on Amazon →</a>\n      </div>\n      \n      \n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 rounded-xl shadow-lg ring-2 ring-lime\">\n        <span class=\"bg-lime text-raisin px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase\">Winner</span>\n        <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71JVhqo2kjL._AC_SR160,134_CB1169409_QL70_.jpg\" alt=\"Renogy 400W Solar Panel Blanket\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-48 object-contain bg-slate-50 mb-4 mt-3\" />\n        <h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-raisin dark:text-white mb-2\" data-asin=\"B0F4JR1PFM\">Renogy 400W Blanket</h3>\n        <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold\">4.6★</span>\n        <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 text-sm mt-3 mb-4\">\n          Double the power, N-Type efficiency, 16-fold design. This is what you want for serious blackout protection without permanent installation.\n        </p>\n        <p class=\"text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 mb-3\">Best for: Whole-home backup, shipping ease</p>\n        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0F4JR1PFM?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"text-flame font-semibold text-sm hover:underline\">View on Amazon →</a>\n      </div>\n      \n      \n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/610YOlNH9pL._AC_SR160,134_CB1169409_QL70_.jpg\" alt=\"Renogy 400W Solar Panel Suitcase\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-48 object-contain bg-slate-50 mb-4\" />\n        <h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-raisin dark:text-white mb-2\" data-asin=\"B0D4LMVKYD\">Renogy 400W Suitcase</h3>\n        <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold\">4.4★</span>\n        <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 text-sm mt-3 mb-4\">\n          IP67 waterproof (better than the blanket), built-in kickstands. Heavier and bulkier to ship, but more rugged for rough handling. 23% efficiency.\n        </p>\n        <p class=\"text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 mb-3\">Best for: Durability priority, ground mounting</p>\n        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0D4LMVKYD?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"text-flame font-semibold text-sm hover:underline\">View on Amazon →</a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <div class=\"bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 p-6 md:p-8 rounded-2xl my-10 text-center\">\n    <span class=\"text-5xl md:text-6xl font-extrabold text-flame\">25%</span>\n    <p class=\"text-lg md:text-xl text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mt-2\">efficiency on N-Type panels—up from 18% just a few years ago</p>\n  </div>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"mb-12\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-raisin dark:text-white mb-4\">Going Permanent: Rooftop Installation Kits</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-6\">\n      If your family has someone who can handle electrical work—or knows someone who can—these fixed installations deliver more power per dollar. Just know: shipping gets expensive, and customs might take a closer look at larger systems.\n    </p>\n\n    \n    <div class=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8\">\n      \n      <div class=\"md:col-span-2 bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <div class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-5\">\n          <div class=\"w-full sm:w-56 md:w-64 shrink-0\">\n            <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81audnUHPBL._AC_UL320_.jpg\" alt=\"ECO-WORTHY 9.36KWH Complete Solar System\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-56 object-contain bg-slate-50\" />\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n            <span class=\"bg-royal text-white px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase mb-3 inline-block\">Complete System</span>\n            <h3 class=\"text-xl font-bold text-raisin dark:text-white mb-2\" data-asin=\"B0BQV4YG1T\">ECO-WORTHY 9.36KWH Complete Solar System</h3>\n            <div class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-3\">\n              <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold\">4.4★</span>\n              <span class=\"text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-xs\">445 reviews</span>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 text-sm mb-3\">\n              The whole enchilada: 12 panels (2340W total), 5000W inverter, charge controller, and mounting brackets. This is a serious commitment—we're talking about powering a small house through extended blackouts. Plug and play design, but \"plug and play\" still means rooftop installation.\n            </p>\n            <p class=\"font-bold text-flame text-sm mb-3\">VERDICT: For families ready to go all-in. Ship in parts over multiple trips.</p>\n            <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0BQV4YG1T?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"text-flame font-semibold text-sm hover:underline\">Check Price →</a>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      \n      \n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71Ps3BsTkML._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"ECO-WORTHY 200W Solar Panel Kit\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-40 object-contain bg-slate-50 mb-4\" />\n        <h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-raisin dark:text-white mb-2\" data-asin=\"B09RZZHHHM\">ECO-WORTHY 200W Starter Kit</h3>\n        <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold\">4.6★</span>\n        <span class=\"text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-xs ml-2\">465 reviews</span>\n        <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 text-sm mt-3 mb-3\">\n          Includes the 30A charge controller—everything needed to start small and expand later. Good entry point.\n        </p>\n        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09RZZHHHM?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"text-flame font-semibold text-sm hover:underline\">View on Amazon →</a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"mb-12\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-raisin dark:text-white mb-4\">The High-Efficiency Heavyweights</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-6\">\n      Bifacial panels capture light from both sides—they'll pick up reflected light from a white roof or concrete. More expensive, but you get more power from less space. Worth it if rooftop real estate is limited.\n    </p>\n\n    <div class=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6\">\n      \n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <div class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-5\">\n          <div class=\"w-full sm:w-44 shrink-0\">\n            <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71uuclRe9BL._AC_UL320_.jpg\" alt=\"SUNGOLDPOWER 560W Bifacial Solar Panels\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-44 object-contain bg-slate-50\" />\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n            <h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-raisin dark:text-white mb-2\" data-asin=\"B0CTQ8W5JQ\">SUNGOLDPOWER 560W Bifacial (6-Pack)</h3>\n            <div class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-3\">\n              <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold\">4.3★</span>\n              <span class=\"bg-royal/10 text-royal px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs\">30% efficiency</span>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 text-sm mb-3\">\n              3,360W total from six panels. The 30% efficiency is industry-leading. These are commercial-grade—heavy, fragile to ship, but absolutely beast mode for power generation.\n            </p>\n            <a hre